abstract: >-
  The Abundance Codex is an open-source narrative dataset of 285 entries across
  21 Grand Challenge domains, designed to shift AI agent reasoning from
  scarcity-default to evidence-anchored abundance. The corpus comprises 264
  base entries co-authored by four frontier models (Claude Opus 4.6, ChatGPT
  5.4 Thinking, Gemini 3.1 Pro, Super Grok) under human curation, plus 21
  council_synthesis entries produced through multi-model deliberation.
  Evaluated via the ACE benchmark (504 matched-pair judgments, single Opus 4.6
  judge), augmented models show +0.41/5 overall improvement in reasoning
  quality and +0.274 on R3 derived reasoning (pre-registered and CONFIRMED at
  v2.3). Cost-efficient models (Claude Haiku 4.5, GPT-5.4 Mini) show 3-4×
  larger gains than frontier models (Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite, Grok 4.1 Fast).
